.TH "radeon_ring_init" 9 "radeon_ring_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
radeon_ring_init \- init driver ring struct.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" radeon_ring_init
.BI "(struct radeon_device *rdev "  ","
.BI "struct radeon_ring *ring "  ","
.BI "unsigned ring_size "  ","
.BI "unsigned rptr_offs "  ","
.BI "u32 nop "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
radeon_device pointer
.IP "ring" 12
radeon_ring structure holding ring information
.IP "ring_size" 12
size of the ring
.IP "rptr_offs" 12
offset of the rptr writeback location in the WB buffer
.IP "nop" 12
nop packet for this ring
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initialize the driver information for the selected ring (all asics).
Returns 0 on success, error on failure.
